<p class="govuk-body">The file upload pattern lets users upload files to an HMRC service. It is optimised for integration with Upscan (the HMRC file upload service).</p>

<h2 class="govuk-heading-l" id="when-to-use">When to use</h2>

<p class="govuk-body">Use this pattern when users must upload a file to complete their journey.</p>

<h2 class="govuk-heading-l" id="when-not-to-use">When not to use</h2>

<p class="govuk-body">Do not use this pattern if there is no need for users to upload a file, or no good reason to ask for one. The interaction of uploading a file can be challenging for some users.</p>

<h2 class="govuk-heading-l" id="how-it-works">How it works</h2>

{{ hmrcFrontendInfo() }}

<p class="govuk-body">How it works depends on whether the user needs the option to upload a single file, more than one file, or select the file type.</p>

<h3 class="govuk-heading-m" id="let-users-upload-a-single-file">Let users upload a single file</h3>

<p class="govuk-body">Use the <a class="govuk-link" href="https://design-system.service.gov.uk/components/file-upload/">file upload component</a> to let users upload a single file.</p>

{{
