    description: 'Let users upload additional files with new row'
  })
}}

<h3 class="govuk-heading-m" id="let-users-select-file-types">Let users select file types</h3>

<p class="govuk-body">If file type selection is required use a question page.</p>

{{
  example({
    item: 'file-upload',
    example: 'types',
    description: 'Optional yes/no question'
  })
}}

<p class="govuk-body">Use a Yes/No question to route the user back to file type selection. Label previous upload rows.</p>

{{
  example({
    item: 'file-upload',
    example: 'question',
    description: 'Optional yes/no question'
  })
}}

<h3 class="govuk-heading-m" id="let-users-upload-a-fixed-set-of-documents">Let users upload a fixed set of documents</h3>

<p class="govuk-body">If multiple specific file uploads are required show labelled upload rows.</p>

{{
  example({
    item: 'file-upload',
    example: 'fixed',
    description: 'Let users upload multiple specifically required files'
  })
}}

<h3 class="govuk-heading-m" id="make-users-aware-of-the-status-of-their-upload">Make users aware of the status of their upload</h3>

<p class="govuk-body">Use a yellow 'UPLOADING' <a class="govuk-link" href="https://design-system.service.gov.uk/components/tag/">tag</a> to show that a file is being uploaded or scanned. When JavaScript isn’t available include ‘Refresh page to update file upload progress’ link to the same page above the summary list.</p>

{{
  example({
    item: 'file-upload',
    example: 'uploading',
    description: 'Uploading'
  })
}}

<p class="govuk-body">Use a green 'UPLOADED' <a class="govuk-link" href="https://design-system.service.gov.uk/components/tag/">tag</a> to show the user that their file has been uploaded and scanned successfully. Announce '[file name] uploaded' in an aria-live region. Link to a copy of the file from the filename..</p>

{{
  example({
    item: 'file-upload',
    example: 'uploaded',
    description: 'Uploaded'
  })
}}

<h4 class="govuk-heading-s">Multiple file uploads (subtitle)</h4>

<p class="govuk-body">Add a polite govuk-visually-hidden aria-live region above the summary list of files ‘X of X files uploaded.’. When JavaScript isn’t available ensure this otherwise visually hidden content is shown.</p>

<h3 class="govuk-heading-m" id="accept-multiple-file-types">Accept multiple file types</h3>

<p class="govuk-body">Let users upload as many different file types as possible. Convert them automatically, if you need to.</p>

<p class="govuk-body">If you must limit file types, let users know by using hint text.</p>

<h3 class="govuk-heading-m" id="error-messages">Error messages</h3>

